Subject: Linux-RT 2.6.25.4-RT
From: http://www.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/projects/rt/
Acked-by: Sven-Thorsten Dietrich <sdietrich@suse.de>
From: Steven Rostedt <srostedt@redhat.com>
Subject: rtmutex - remove double xchg

No reason to update current if we are running. We'll do that when we exit
the loop.

Signed-off-by: Steven Rostedt <srostedt@redhat.com>
---
 kernel/rtmutex.c |    2 --
 1 file changed, 2 deletions(-)

Index: linux-2.6.25.4-rt4/kernel/rtmutex.c
===================================================================
--- linux-2.6.25.4-rt4.orig/kernel/rtmutex.c	2008-05-29 09:47:24.000000000 -0400
+++ linux-2.6.25.4-rt4/kernel/rtmutex.c	2008-05-29 09:47:24.000000000 -0400
@@ -748,8 +748,6 @@ rt_spin_lock_slowlock(struct rt_mutex *l
 		update_current(TASK_UNINTERRUPTIBLE, &saved_state);
 		if (waiter.task)
 			schedule_rt_mutex(lock);
-		else
-			update_current(TASK_RUNNING_MUTEX, &saved_state);
 
 		spin_lock_irqsave(&lock->wait_lock, flags);
 		current->flags |= saved_flags;
